In a speech at the East Room, President Biden discussed the Inflation Reduction Act and its impact on lowering prescription drug prices. He emphasized the need to give Medicare the power to negotiate lower prices and highlighted the high cost of prescription drugs in the United States compared to other countries. The President also mentioned the efforts of Big Pharma to block the legislation and the ongoing fight against them. He announced that Medicare has selected 10 additional drugs for negotiation under the Inflation Reduction Act, which will benefit millions of Americans. President Biden also touched on other healthcare initiatives, such as capping out-of-pocket costs for seniors and cracking down on surprise medical bills. He concluded by expressing his optimism for America's future and the importance of working together.